org.jeo.sql

Class FilterSQLEncoder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jeo.filter.FilterVisitor
      • org.jeo.sql.FilterSQLEncoder
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    GeoPkgFilterSQLEncoder, PostGISFilterEncoder

    public class FilterSQLEncoder
extends FilterVisitor
    Transforms a filter object into SQL.

    This base implementation encodes using "standard" SQL and SFS (simple features for SQL) conventions. Format implementations should subclass and override methods as need be.

    The encoder operates in two modes in one of two modes determined by isPrepared(). When true the encoder will emit prepared statement sql. Arguments for the prepared statement are stored in getArgs(). When false the encoder will encode literals directly.

    Author:
    Justin Deoliveira, OpenGeo
